news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM outlines plan for a new urban redevelopment policy that rejuvenates cities
news.para: In a significant move, Uttar Pradesh is rolling out a groundbreaking urban redevelopment strategy. The proposed policy seeks to revitalize urban areas with state-of-the-art infrastructure and essential public services. Central to this initiative is the strategic overhaul of land use paired with incentives for private sector contributions.

news.title: Sunac China says most creditors approve restructuring plan
news.para: Sunac China has successfully garnered approval from most creditors for its offshore debt restructuring strategy, a vital move designed to shore up its financial stability during the ongoing slump in the property market. This ambitious plan addresses nearly $8 billion of the company's overseas debt, with final court endorsement on the horizon.

news.title: SC seeks replies of Centre, SEBI on Sahara firm's plea for nod to sell properties to Adani
news.para: The Supreme Court is examining Sahara India Commercial Corporation Ltd's request to sell 88 prime properties, including Amby Valley, to Adani Properties Private Limited. The court has asked the Centre, SEBI, and other stakeholders to respond by November 17. The amicus curiae will collate details of the properties, noting any disputes.

news.title: SC restores 213 flats of Udaipur-based project after ED proactively helps homebuyers
news.para: Home buyers of Project Royal Rajvilas received relief as the Supreme Court released their flats. The apex court also ended the Enforcement Directorate's challenge to the insolvency process. This decision helps over 200 buyers whose dream homes were stalled for 12 years. The court praised the ED's efforts in securing the buyers' interests.

news.title: CCI okays Vedanta's proposal to acquire Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: The Competition Commission of India has officially sanctioned Vedanta's substantial bid for Jaiprakash Associates, an important advancement in the company's insolvency journey. Vedanta's offer of ₹17,000 crore has received initial approval, competing against proposals from notable players such as Jindal Power and Adani Group.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 26-acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: Godrej Properties has acquired a 26-acre land parcel near Sarjapur Road in South Bengaluru. The company intends to develop a premium residential project on this site, projecting a revenue potential of ₹1,100 crore. This acquisition highlights the Sarjapur Road corridor's significance as a key growth hub in Bengaluru's real estate market.

news.title: Anant Raj raises ₹1,100 crore by selling shares to investors
news.para: Anant Raj Ltd has successfully raised Rs 1,100 crore by issuing equity shares to institutional investors. The Finance and Investment Committee approved the allotment of over 1.66 crore shares at Rs 662 each to qualified institutional buyers. The company, a prominent developer of housing, commercial projects, and data centers, saw its shares close at Rs 657.75 on Tuesday.

news.title: Bellway CEO calls for end to stamp duty to revive UK housing sector
news.para: Prominent UK home construction companies are urging the government to eliminate stamp duty for first-time buyers. Additionally, they advocate for a lasting deposit scheme designed to assist young adults in breaking into the housing market. This initiative arises amid growing affordability concerns and a dip in consumer confidence.

news.title: Austrian former property tycoon Rene Benko goes on trial for fraud
news.para: Rene Benko, the ex-billionaire from Austria, is currently under scrutiny in Innsbruck, facing his first trial connected to the dramatic downfall of his property company, Signa. Authorities allege deceptive practices leading to an astounding 300 million euros in losses, painting a picture of financial misconduct that includes disputed rental fees and a controversial gift to his mother.

news.title: Strata exits Express Zone, Mumbai at ₹40 crore with 13% IRR
news.para: Strata has successfully exited its premium office investment in Express Zone, Goregaon East, Mumbai, for ₹40 crore. Acquired in March 2021 for ₹33.6 crore and fractionalized among 120 investors, the asset yielded 13% IRR and 20% capital appreciation. Investors also received ₹12.9 crore in rental disbursements during the holding period.

news.title: One Prastha Realty raises ₹80 crore from Capri Global to fund township project
news.para: One Prastha Realty has secured Rs 80 crore debt from Capri Global. This funding will support the development of a 57-acre integrated township in Sonipat, Haryana. The project includes residential plots and villas. This capital will accelerate project delivery and enable expansion.

news.title: Shubhashish Homes posts pre-sales of over ₹250 crore in H1 FY26
news.para: Shubhashish Homes, the real estate division of JK Jajoo Ventures, has surpassed last year's full-year pre-sales by reporting over ₹250 crore in the first half of FY 2025-26. The company is well-positioned to meet its ₹400 crore pre-sales target for the year. New project launches in Indore and Prayagraj are anticipated in Q4 FY26, pending necessary approvals.

news.title: Prayagraj development body's urban expansion plan to include 200 new villages
news.para: Prayagraj Development Authority (PDA) has proposed an urban expansion plan, increasing its jurisdiction to 1,278 square kilometers by incorporating approximately 200 new villages. This initiative aims to boost revenue through increased taxes and fees, which will fund city development. The expanded boundaries will now extend near the Ganga Expressway.

news.title: HouseEazy raises ₹150 crore in series B round led by Accel
news.para: HouseEazy has secured ₹150 crore in a Series B funding round led by Accel, with existing investors also participating. This capital will drive technological advancements, geographic expansion into new cities, and brand growth. The company's GMV ARR has doubled year-on-year to ₹850 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra: I-T department plans to penalise sub-registrar offices for not reporting real estate transactions
news.para: The income tax department is set to penalize property sub-registrar offices across the region. These offices failed to report real estate deals worth Rs13,000 crore in their financial transaction statements. This under-reporting helps individuals evade taxes. The department is finalizing penalties, which could run into lakhs for each office. The state revenue department will then decide on responsibility and payment.

news.title: South Goa residents told to flag unsafe buildings
news.para: South Goa Collector Egna Cleetus has issued a public notice, urging residents to report unsafe or dilapidated buildings. Citizens should inform local municipalities or block development officers about structurally weak premises. The administration emphasizes owner responsibility and advises against occupying such buildings due to visible risks. For emergencies, contact the South Goa Collectorate Control Room at 0832-2794100.

news.title: Maharashtra collects ₹29,795 crore in property registrations fees till October 12
news.para: Maharashtra's property registrations remain strong, collecting nearly half its annual target in stamp duty and registration fees despite a recent hike in ready reckoner rates. Robust high-value transactions and a buoyant real estate market have driven this growth, with officials confident of exceeding the target.

news.title: CLSA sells 8.4 lakh shares in WeWork India Management for ₹52 crore
news.para: Global markets company CLSA sold over 8 lakh shares in WeWork India Management on Monday. The deal size reached Rs 52 crore. WeWork India shares continued their decline for a second day. The stock is trading below its IPO price. The company's recent IPO saw lukewarm response from retail investors. Qualified Institutional Buyers drove the subscription.

news.title: Ramabai Nagar redevelopment to begin in Mumbai on October 14
news.para: The redevelopment of Ramabai Ambedkar Nagar and Kamraj Nagar in Ghatkopar is set to begin. The mega project will transform the area into a planned housing cluster with over 17,000 homes. Phase I will construct 4,345 tenements. Families will be relocated within the same area. The project includes community facilities and will integrate with the city's transport network.

news.title: Delhi HC refuses to restrain property sale due to frivolous litigation
news.para: Delhi High Court ruled that frivolous cases cannot be used to harass property owners, allowing a sale despite a "fragile claim" from a realtor. The court imposed a Rs 5 lakh cost, stating the law can exempt properties from restrictions in such litigations to prevent misuse of judicial processes and protect genuine owners.
